@10001 = ~Enrage

Duration: Special
Area of Effect: The caster

The character becomes enraged for 1 turn. While enraged, the character gains a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls as well as to Armor Class, and becomes immune to charm, confusion, fear, feeblemind, hold, imprisonment, level drain, maze, stun, and sleep. The character also gains 15 temporary Hit Points which are taken away at the end of the berserk spree, possibly killing the character. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative. After the effects end, the character becomes winded, suffering a -2 penalty to Armor Class, to-hit rolls, and damage rolls.~
@10002 = ~Kai

Duration: 10 seconds
Area of Effect: The caster

All successful attacks within the next 10 seconds deal maximum damage.~
@10003 = ~Barbarian Rage

Duration: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

The enraged status lasts for 5 rounds and provides a +4 bonus to Strength and Constitution, a -2 penalty to Armor Class and a +2 bonus to Saving Throws vs. spell, as well as immunity to all charm, hold, fear, maze, stun, sleep, confusion, and level drain spells. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.~
@10004 = ~Lay On Hands

Range: Touch
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature

The character channels positive energy to heal the touched creature of 2 Hit Points per level of the caster.~
@10005 = ~Detect Evil

Range: 0
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 60-ft. radius
Saving Throw: None

This ability discovers emanations of evil from any creature. Any evil creature within the range of the ability will glow red briefly.~
@10006 = ~Protection From Evil

Range: Touch
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature

When this ability is cast, it creates a magical barrier around the recipient at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the recipient and has two major effects: First, all attacks made by evil or evilly enchanted creatures against the protected creature receive a penalty of -2 to each attack roll. Second, summoned demons cannot target the protected creature.~
@10007 = ~Remove Fear

Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius

The character instills courage in the ability's recipients, raising their morale to its highest. The recipients' morale will gradually reset to normal as the duration runs out. If the recipients are affected by magical fear, this is negated.~
@10008 = ~Dispel Magic

Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: None

This ability removes magical effects upon anyone within the area and acts at twice the character level. This includes effects given from spells, potions and certain magical items such as wands.~
@10009 = ~True Sight

Range: 0
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 235-ft. radius
Saving Throw: None

Instantly and once each round for 1 turn after this ability is cast, all hostile Illusion/Phantasm spells in a 235-ft. radius around the caster will be dispelled. The target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not affect this.~
@10010 = ~Charm Animal

Range: Touch
Duration: 2 turns
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Negates effect

This ability affects any single animal it is cast upon. The animal is allowed a save vs. spell to negate the effect. If the ability's recipient fails its Saving Throw, it regards the caster as a trusted friend and ally to be heeded and protected. The caster may give it orders, and the charmed animal will carry them out as quickly as possible. If the caster harms, or attempts to harm, the charmed animal by some overt action, or if a Dispel Magic spell is cast upon the charmed animal, the ability is broken. If two or more charms simultaneously affect a creature, the most recent charm takes precedence. Note that the subject will be hostile when the charm expires, regardless of its original attitude. Also note that you cannot have a charmed creature leave the area where it was charmed.~
@10011 = ~Called Shot

Duration: 10 seconds
Area of Effect: The caster

All successful ranged attacks within the next 10 seconds have the following cumulative effects besides normal damage, according to the level of the caster:
  4th Level: -1 penalty to target's THAC0
  8th Level: -1 penalty to target's Saving Throws vs. spell
  12th Level: -1 penalty to target's Strength score
  16th Level: +2 bonus to damage roll~
@10012 = ~Find Familiar

Range: 20 yards
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Special

This ability enables the caster to attempt to summon a familiar to act as his aide and companion. Familiars are typically small creatures. A creature acting as a familiar can benefit a caster, conveying its sensory powers to its master, conversing with him, and serving as a guard/scout/spy as well. A caster can have only one familiar at a time, and he has no control over what sort of creature answers the summoning, if any come at all. The creature is always more intelligent than others of its type (typically by 2 or 3 Intelligence points), and its bond with the caster confers upon it an exceptionally long life. The caster has an empathic link with the familiar and can issue it mental commands. The caster receives half the familiar's total Hit Points (rounded down) as bonus Hit Points. However, the caster must take care to treat his familiar well, for if the familiar should die, the caster loses the bonus Hit Points and the familiar's Hit Points again as damage. Also when a familiar dies, the caster loses 1 point of Constitution PERMANENTLY.

Here is a list of the familiars that the protagonist receives according to alignment:

LAWFUL GOOD, NEUTRAL GOOD: Pseudo Dragon
 - Hit Points: 24
 - Armor Class: -2
 - 50% resistance to magic
 - Regenerates 1 Hit Point per round
 - Can cast Blur once per day
 - Immune to level drain, sleep, and petrification
 - Combat: 2 attacks per round at 17 THAC0 for 1d3 piercing damage, hit target must save vs. death at -1 or be rendered unconscious for 2 turns

CHAOTIC GOOD: Fairy Dragon
 - Hit Points: 24
 - Armor Class: 4
 - 32% resistance to magic
 - Can cast Mirror Image and Minor Mass Invisibility once per day
 - Immune to level drain, sleep, and petrification
 - Combat: 2 attacks per round at 17 THAC0 for 1d2 slashing damage~
@10013 = ~Set Snare

Range: 1 yard
Duration: Permanent until triggered
Area of Effect: 1 creature within a 35-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Special

Set a trap in the chosen location when no hostile creatures are in sight. Traps grow more powerful with the character's level and can only be triggered by enemies.
  1st level: Deals 2d8 +5 missile damage.
  11th level: Deals 2d8 +5 missile damage and additionally deals 2d6 poison damage per round for the next 3 rounds.
  16th level: Deals 3d8 +5 missile damage and 4d8 +2 fire damage.
  21st level: Deals 3d8 +5 missile damage and 20 poison damage with no save; slays target if a save vs. death with a +4 bonus is failed.~
@10014 = ~Poison Weapon

Duration: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

Each successful hit within the next round will inject poison into the target, dealing an extra 2 points of damage per second with no Saving Throw (for a total of 12 points of damage). Moreover, if the target fails a Saving Throw vs. poison, he will suffer 1 additional point of damage per second for 4 rounds. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.~
@10015 = ~Set Special Snare

Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: Permanent until triggered
Area of Effect: 1 creature within a 35-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Special

Set a trap in the chosen location when no hostile creatures are in sight. Traps grow more powerful with the character's level and can only be triggered by enemies.
  1st level: Deals 3d8 +5 missile damage and slows target for 5 rounds if a save vs. spell with a -4 penalty is failed
  11th level: Deals 4d8 +5 missile damage and holds target for 5 rounds if a save vs. spell with a -1 penalty is failed
  16th level: Erects an Otiluke's Resilient Sphere around the target for 7 rounds if a save vs. spell is failed
  21st level: Mazes the target~
@10016 = ~Storm Shield

Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: The caster

This ability lasts 1 round per level of the caster. It protects the caster completely from lightning, fire, cold, and normal missiles.~
@10017 = ~Lightning Bolt

Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: Instant
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Path of bolt
Saving Throw: 1/2

Upon casting this ability, the caster releases a powerful stroke of electrical energy that inflicts 1d6 points of damage per level of the caster (maximum damage of 10d6) to each creature within its area of effect. A successful Saving Throw vs. spell reduces this damage to half. If the lightning bolt intersects with a wall, it will bounce until it reaches its full length.~
@10018 = ~Seeking Sword

Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: The caster

This ability creates a sword in the character's hand that cannot be dropped or unequipped. The sword is enchanted as a +4 weapon and provides a +4 THAC0 bonus, but no damage bonus. It deals 2d4 damage to any target it hits. The weapon sets the character's number of attacks per round to 3 and lasts for 1 round per level. While it is equipped, the wielder cannot cast further spells.~
@10019 = ~Boon of Lathander

Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: The caster

This ability lasts 1 round per level of the caster. It gives the caster a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls, a +1 bonus to all Saving Throws, and 1 extra attack per round. It also protects the caster from level drain.~
@10020 = ~Hold Undead

Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 2 rounds/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Negates effect

This ability holds 1d4 undead creatures rigidly immobile and in place. The effect is centered on the victim selected by the caster. Any enemies within 7.5 ft. of the target are also affected. Those who succeed on their Saving Throws are totally unaffected by the ability. Held creatures cannot move or speak, but they remain aware of events around them and can use abilities not requiring motion or speech. Being held does not prevent the worsening of the subject's condition due to wounds.~
@10021 = ~Offensive Spin

Duration: 4 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

During the next 4 rounds, the character's movement rate doubles and the character gains a +2 bonus to hit and damage rolls as well as an extra attack per round. All attacks deal maximum damage for the duration. Offensive Spin may not be used in conjunction with the Haste or Improved Haste spells. It does not stack with Defensive Spin. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.~
@10022 = ~Defensive Spin

Duration: 4 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

During the next 4 rounds, the character is rooted to the spot and gains a +1 bonus to Armor Class per level, up to a maximum of +10. It does not stack with Offensive Spin. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.~
