@10033 = ~Breathe Fireball

Range: 15 yards
Duration: Instant
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This ability launches a flaming projectile at a single target, dealing 2d6 fire damage on a successful ranged attack.~
@10034 = ~Stunning Blow

Duration: 9 seconds
Area of Effect: The caster

All successful attacks within the next round force the victim to save vs. spell or be stunned for 9 seconds. This special ability automatically modifies normal attacks; no targeting needs to be done.~
@10035 = ~Lay On Hands

Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: The caster

The character channels positive energy to heal himself of 2 Hit Points per level.~
@10036 = ~Quivering Palm

Duration: 5 seconds
Area of Effect: The caster

The next successful attack forces the opponent to save vs. spell or die. This special ability automatically modifies normal attacks; no targeting needs to be done.~
@10037 = ~Set Spike Trap

Range: 1 yard
Duration: Permanent until triggered
Area of Effect: 1 creature within a 30-ft. radius
Saving Throw: None

This ability allows the rogue to set a powerful spring-loaded spike trap that does 20d6 magical damage to the unsuspecting creature that sets it off.~
@10038 = ~Set Exploding Trap

Range: 1 yard
Duration: Permanent until triggered
Area of Effect: 40-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Special

This ability allows the rogue to set a powerful trap that unleashes a fireball which causes 10d6 fire damage (save vs. spell for half damage) and will knock its victims off their feet.~
@10039 = ~Set Time Trap

Range: 1 yard
Duration: Permanent until triggered
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This ability allows the rogue to set a magical trap that casts a weaker version of the high-level Time Stop spell. For 10 seconds, the flow of time slows for all but the rogue. Often, a rogue will use this trap to get behind an opponent for a free attack.~
@10040 = ~Evasion

Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

A rogue's natural sense of preservation becomes heightened with the use of the Evasion ability. Evasion gives a bonus of 4 to Armor Class and 2 to all Saving Throws. The effect lasts for 3 rounds. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.~
@10041 = ~Greater Evasion

Duration: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

A more powerful version of Evasion, this ability improves Armor Class by 6 and Saving Throws by 3. In addition, Greater Evasion allows the rogue to move so quickly that his movement rate is increased by 2 and normal missiles have no chance of striking him. Greater Evasion lasts for 5 rounds. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.

Requires: Evasion~
@10042 = ~Avoid Death

Duration: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster

With extraordinary effort, a high-level rogue can avoid almost certain death. The effect lasts for 5 rounds, and during this time, the rogue's save vs. death receives a bonus of 5, Hit Points are increased by 20, and the rogue becomes immune to death magic. Multiple usages of this ability are not cumulative.~
@10043 = ~Alchemy

Duration: Permanent
Area of Effect: The caster

With cleverness innate to the class, an experienced rogue has seen enough potions in his or her adventuring career to simulate the creation of one. With the Alchemy skill, the rogue can create one of eight types of potions once per day. The potions a rogue can create are randomly chosen from the following list:
1) Potion of Master Thievery
2) Potion of Perception
3) Potion of Extra Healing
4) Potion of Superior Healing
5) Potion of Regeneration
6) Antidote
7) Oil of Speed
8) Rogue's Potion of Frost Giant Strength~
